HEADWORD: arui
<hw>arui</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a wild sheep
(<spn>Ammotragus lervia</spn>) of northern Africa, having a thick mane
on the throat, chest, and forelegs; -- also called the
<altname>aoudad</altname> and <altname>Barbary
sheep</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> aoudad, audad, Barbary sheep, maned sheep.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

